&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPIRATORY MEDICINE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Band 5 Staff Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respiratory Intervention Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you tired of working weekends, nights, bank holidays? If so, then this could be the job for you!!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Respiratory Intervention Service at the John Radcliffe Hospital currently has a vacancy for a band 5 staff nurse. We are a small friendly team who are looking for the ideal person to come and work with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated nurse to work in our specialist respiratory department - you will be required to rotate through the recovery area and into our procedure room. In return, we will provide full training and support to help develop your respiratory knowledge and skills, including assisting medical staff with bronchoscopy, thoracoscopy and IPC insertion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide training for other pleural procedures and support you to become competent in the management of chest drains. You will also be recovery trained for post sedation patients with the opportunity for General Anaesthetic recovery training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be able to demonstrate previous acute experience, possess excellent assessment skills and value the need for efficient communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours for this service are Monday – Friday, with variable hours on each day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are highly recommended.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this opportunity further, please contact Sister Clare Wilkins, Deputy Sister Michaela Fox or Deputy Sister Sarah Woodfin – 01865 222686.&lt;/p&gt;
